# BROWSER-article.md - Article Publish Patterns

**Article editor URL:** `https://x.com/compose/articles`
**Editor type:** Draft.js (`public-DraftEditor-content`)

---

## Key Constraints

- 🚨 **Title:** `textarea[name="Article Title"]` — use clipboard paste via evaluate
- 🚨 **Body:** `div[data-testid="composer"][contenteditable="true"]` — use ClipboardEvent paste with `text/html`
- 🚨 **`execCommand('insertText')` does NOT persist** — Draft.js only saves the last block
- 🚨 **Paste ONLY works on a fresh editor after typing the title.** Do NOT `selectAll`+`delete` before pasting — breaks multi-block creation. Always create a NEW article draft.
- 🚨 **Publish is two clicks:** editor "Publish" → confirm dialog "Publish" (`aria-label="Publish"`)

---

## Supported HTML → Draft.js Mapping

| HTML | Draft.js Class | Visual |
|------|---------------|--------|
| `<h2>` | `longform-header-two` | **Heading** |
| `<p>` | `longform-unstyled` | Body paragraph |
| `<strong>` | `font-weight: bold` (inline) | **Bold** text |
| `<em>` | `font-style: italic` (inline) | *Italic* text |
| `<ul><li>` | `longform-unordered-list-item` | Bullet list |
| `<blockquote>` | `longform-blockquote` | Blockquote |
| `<a href="https://x.com/handle">@handle</a>` | Auto-linked mention | Clickable @mention (notifies user) |
| `#hashtag` (plain text) | Auto-detected by editor | Clickable hashtag link |
| `<a href="https://...">text</a>` | Inline link | Clickable external link |

---

## Step 1 — Navigate to Articles and create new draft

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"https://x.com/compose/articles"}' 2>&1

exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); const createBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label=\"create\"]'); if (createBtn) { createBtn.click(); return { clicked: 'create' }; } const writeBtn = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"empty_state_button_text\"]') || Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('a, button')).find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Write'); if (writeBtn) { writeBtn.click(); return { clicked: 'write' }; } return { error: 'no Write/create button' }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
Wait 3s for editor to load — URL changes to /compose/articles/edit/{id}

---

## Step 2 — Type title (clipboard paste via evaluate)

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var title = document.querySelector('textarea[name=\"Article Title\"]'); if (!title) return { error: 'no title field' }; title.focus(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', '${articleTitle}'); title.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); return { typed: title.value || title.innerText }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

🚨 Title MUST be typed before body paste — this initializes the Draft.js editor for multi-block paste.

---

## Step 3 — Paste body with rich HTML

Build HTML string with formatting, mentions, hashtags. Then paste:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var editor = document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"composer\"]'); if (!editor) return { error: 'no editor' }; editor.focus(); editor.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var html = ${articleHtml}; var plain = ${articlePlainText}; var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', plain); dt.setData('text/html', html); editor.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var result = editor.innerText; var blockCount = editor.querySelectorAll('[data-block]').length; return { pasted: true, wordCount: result.split(/\\s+/).length, blocks: blockCount }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

Wait 5s after paste for auto-save before publishing.

---

## Step 4 — Publish (two-click flow)

**Click 1 — Open publish dialog:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var publishBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Publish'); if (!publishBtn) return { error: 'no publish button' }; publishBtn.click(); return { clicked: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

Wait 2s. Dialog shows: audience (default "Everyone"), reply settings, timeline preview.

**Click 2 — Confirm publish:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var publishBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Publish' && b.getAttribute('aria-label') === 'Publish'); if (!publishBtn) return { error: 'no dialog publish button' }; publishBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5000)); return { published: true, url: window.location.href }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

After publish: page redirects to `https://x.com/{handle}/status/{id}`. Article URL: `https://x.com/{handle}/article/{id}`.

---

## Step 5 — Verify and log

Check `window.location.href` contains `/status/`. Extract article URL by replacing `/status/` with `/article/`.

