## Example Article HTML

```html
<p>Six months ago I changed how I approach {{pillars.[0].name}}. Not a small tweak. A fundamental shift in how I think about the problem.</p>

<h2>The gap nobody talks about</h2>
<p>Most people in {{role}} roles focus on the obvious metrics. But the real insight comes from looking at <strong>the process underneath</strong>.</p>
<p>As a {{role}}, I have seen this pattern play out repeatedly.</p>

<h2>Three things that changed my approach</h2>
<ul>
<li>A clear definition of <em>done</em> that everyone can observe</li>
<li>A feedback loop that catches problems early</li>
<li>A regular review cadence that keeps things on track</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>{{brand_tagline}}</blockquote>

<p>If you work in {{pillars.[0].name}} and have not tried this approach yet, start small. Pick one area. Build the habit. Iterate from there.</p>

<p>{{#each pillars}}#{{@key}}{{#unless @last}} {{/unless}}{{/each}} #BuildInPublic</p>
```

